algocompiler
============

Usage:
  algocompiler <input.alg|input.txt> <output.c>

Example:
  algocompiler program.alg program.c

Install (Debian/Ubuntu):
  1) Put the .deb file in a folder (Downloads, Desktop, etc.)
  2) cd into that folder and check the file exists:
       ls -l *.deb
  3) Install:
       sudo apt update
       sudo apt install -y ./algocompiler_1.0.0_<arch>.deb
     (Replace <arch> with amd64 or arm64 depending on your system.)

Notes:
  - This compiler runs multiple phases and also invokes gcc to build the final executable.
  - If gcc is missing, install it (Debian/Ubuntu):
      sudo apt update && sudo apt install -y gcc

